tafsir[8]{c,v,t}:
  26,189,"They continued rejecting him and so a grave punishment afflicted them by way of a cloud appearing after a severely hot day. It rained a fire upon them that burned them. The day they were destroyed was an extremely horrific day."
  26,193,"It was revealed through the trustworthy Gabriel (peace be upon him)."
  26,194,"O Messenger! He revealed it upon your heart so that you become one of the Messengers who warn the people and make them fearful of the punishment of Allah."
  26,195,"He revealed it in clear Arabic language."
  26,196,"And indeed this Qur’ān has been referenced in the previous Books; the previous divine books have given glad tidings of it."
  26,198,"Had we revealed this Qur’ān upon one of the non-Arabs who do not speak Arabic."
  26,202,"This punishment will come to them suddenly and unexpectedly."
  26,206,"26:205"